DATA CLOUD
Share Data with Google BigQuery Using Zero Copy Integration

You can access Data Cloud objects as datasets in Google BigQuery by creating a data share. Zero-copy integration allows data to be directly shared and queried without copying it into Google BigQuery. When data is accessible in Google BigQuery, you can work with harmonized and unified data from Data Cloud. Sharing data involves these high-level steps.

Before you begin:

Review Data Shares availability in Google BigQuery for Data Cloud Regions.
If you use VPC Service Controls and if the Analytics Hub API is restricted, then create an egress rule in the VPC Service Controls Perimeter to include the Salesforce Analytics Hub Producer project. For more information, see Analytics Hub VPC Service Controls rules.
Identify the Data Cloud objects that you want to access.
Create a data share in Data Cloud.
See Create a Data Share.
Establish connectivity with Google BigQuery by creating a data share target in Data Cloud.
See Create a Data Share Target to Connect with Google BigQuery.
Link the data share with the data share target to make the Data Cloud objects accessible in BigQuery.
See Link or Unlink Data Shares and Data Share Targets.
In Google BigQuery subscribe to the Data Cloud data shares using the Analytics hub.
Create a Data Share Target to Connect with Google BigQuery
To establish connectivity with a Google BigQuery account, create a data share target in Data Cloud.
Data Shares availability in Google BigQuery for Data Cloud Regions
At present Data Cloud integration with Google BigQuery in these AWS regions.
Subscribe to Data Shares in Google Analytics Hub
The Google Cloud users can subscribe to the data using the Analytics Hub.
